The film introduces the characters with a quick bio line then jumps to a bank robbery. They get away with $850,000 as cops chase them along with helicopters. Lucky (John Azpilicueta) manages to outrun them and radio as he shifts gears in his automatic Mercury Cougar. The film eventually degrades into a series of home break-ins with flash backs as bad guys comb the houses looking for them after news reports.

The film was flat as the character introduction was meaningless to have us connect to the bank robbers, our protagonists. The acting and dialogue was bland. It couldn't hold my interest.

Parental Guide: F-bomb, sex, rape, nudity
